-- China, North Korea Urge Efforts For Resumption of Six-Party Nuclear Talks
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-16T00:20:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-16/china-north-korea-urge-efforts-for-resumption-of-six-party-nuclear-talks.html
China and North Korea urged efforts
from related parties to start the six-party nuclear talks,
according to a statement posted on China’s Foreign Ministry
website yesterday. Wu Dawei, China’s special representative for
Korean Peninsula affairs, held talks with North Korea’s First
Vice Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Kye Gwan on Oct. 12 and 15.
The countries agreed to keep pushing for progress in the six-
party talks, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
